Youssou N'Dour - Rokku Mi Rokka (Give And Take)
2007

Brought to you by TQMP
The Quality Music Project

&quot;Sometimes you will hear a little blues on the album, a little reggae, a bit of Cuba. In Africa, we get excited when we hear these rhythms, because we feel them, they are ours, but they left Africa with the slaves a long time ago. Rokku Mi Rokka means 'You give me something, I give you something' and that's the message of the album: we have received a lot from the developed world, but remember that we brought a lot, too.&quot;
